Topic:		language/yacc

Description:	The Yacc Programming Language

Notes:

  Yacc (and its GNU descendent, bison) is a generator of parsing code.  It
  translates a syntax description (akin to a BNF grammar) and snippets of C
  code into a compilable set of C routines for scanning a stream of tokens
  and parsing for meaningful expressions.

